title: For Sale/Trade:  Deer Season Is Almost Here.....
location: South, in Beloit, WI, Janesville, Wisconsin
postcontent:
For sale is a 1987 production Sturm, Ruger & Co., Inc. Mini-Thirty assault rifle in 7.62x39mm caliber.  It is constructed of alloy steel with traditional blued finish, and the 16” barrel has a 6-groove bore and a 1:10” RH twist, which is better suited to a heavier bullet than a standard 123gr 7.62x39 (Russian SKS and AK-47).

 The rifle has a Hammers SF2-8x26CE scope with elevation, windage and distance focus adjustments, and flip-up lens covers.

The furniture is a military grade TAPCO modular INTRAFUSE Mini-Thirty stock system.  The fore-end features a top barrel cover with an integral Picatinny single rail, and an integral bottom Picatinny rail with cover for the addition of a vertical fore-grip or other accessories.  The butt-stock is identical to the TAPCO T6, adjustable to 6 positions and includes the sling ring.  An integrated TAPCO style composite pistol grip with storage completes the system.

An adjustable bench-rest height Harris bipod with sling and rail mounts is attached to the under-rail of the fore-stock.  In front of the bipod is an Omega Tactical E.T.G. XP-6E combination laser/flashlight unit with independent laser and light function and remote pressure switch, mounted under the barrel with a Leapers UTG Universal single rail barrel mount. 

The rifle comes with six magazines, 3 of which are 30-rnd black composite Ruger-matched ProMags.  The other three magazines are Sturm Ruger factory steel mags, 1-10 rnd, 1-20 rnd, and 1-30 rnd.  The rifle also comes with a NcStar digital camouflage soft side carry case with sling and five external magazine pockets. 

Despite the production year, the rifle is barely broken in with less than 40 rounds down the pipe, and is a great deer rifle.  I can get 3” groupings out of it at 200 yards with a 147-154gr cartridge and minor drop adjustment to the scope, but a more patient shooter could probably tighten that up a bit. 

I am selling the rifle with all accessories for a FIRM $1,100.00 cash, or $850 without the scope, bipod and laser.  Buyer must have a valid Wisconsin ID (driver’s license) or CCL, and complete the transaction face to face (I will NOT ship the rifle).
